# Import Path: Prefer @/ Alias

Use the **`@/`** path alias for imports unless there is a good reason to use a relative path.

## Prefer

```ts
import { Button } from '@/components/atomics/button';
import { useCart } from '@/core/store';
import { formatPrice } from '@/utils/format';
```

## Avoid (unless necessary)

```ts
import { Button } from '../../../components/atomics/button';
import { useCart } from '../../../../core/store';
```

## When relative paths are acceptable

- **Same directory / colocated files**: `./LocalComponent`, `./styles.css`, `./constants`
- **Package has no `@/`**: In packages or apps where `tsconfig` does not define the `@/*` alias

